weird things that don't fit together.

161
00:09:37.430 --> 00:09:39.307
I think product managers are necessary.

162
00:09:39.307 --> 00:09:44.870
That might be my own bias showing
here a little bit, right?

163
00:09:44.870 --> 00:09:48.118
So, it's gonna depend on,
does your team have a product manager and

164
00:09:48.118 --> 00:09:50.247
your product manager
is not helping enough?

165
00:09:50.247 --> 00:09:53.740
Is it that your team doesn't have one and
it needs one?

166
00:09:53.740 --> 00:09:55.550
It's gonna depend.

167
00:09:55.550 --> 00:10:02.056
But I do see frequently engineers
do have to act as mini PMs.

168
00:10:02.056 --> 00:10:03.871
I liked it when I was an engineer, and

169
00:10:03.871 --> 00:10:06.343
I think that's why I liked
being a PM eventually.

170
00:10:06.343 --> 00:10:11.212
But I liked having a lot of say in
what we build as opposed to just being

171
00:10:11.212 --> 00:10:12.672
told what to build.

